This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new evaluation metric for Generative Adversarial Networks (GANs) based on the intrinsic dimensionality of the data space learned by the GAN model. The paper also conducts experiments on benchmark image datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). Additionally, the paper involves the use of artificial intelligence techniques to improve GAN generation quality, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also involves the use of neural networks, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of GANs, which could place it in the sub-category of cs.GR (Graphics).
